Speed brakes extended.

364
00:24:21,982 --> 00:24:24,245
反向全速推进。反向全速推进。
Reverse full thrust. Reverse full thrust.

365
00:24:26,029 --> 00:24:28,336
-帮我踩刹车，德勒。-这就去。
- Help me with the brakes, Dele. - On it.

366
00:24:56,320 --> 00:24:57,321
好的。
Okay.

367
00:24:58,932 --> 00:25:00,847
一切了。
Everything off.

368
00:25:04,503 --> 00:25:06,374
如何……你怎么…
How... How did you...

369
00:25:11,292 --> 00:25:12,511
一次一分钟。
One minute at a time.

370
00:25:13,381 --> 00:25:15,296
删除?
Right, Dele?

371
00:25:18,560 --> 00:25:19,822
他妈的。
Fuck.

372
00:25:23,565 --> 00:25:25,045
见鬼，我们还有燃料。
Hell, we still got fuel.

373
00:25:25,698 --> 00:25:27,438
还有一架热飞机。
And a hot plane.

374
00:25:27,482 --> 00:25:29,789
让大家都下车吧。我们走吧。
Let's get everyone off now. Let's go.

375
00:25:29,832 --> 00:25:31,138
德勒，让所有人到前面去。
Dele, get everybody in the front.

376
00:25:31,181 --> 00:25:33,053
把我弄下这该死的飞机。
Get me the hell off this damn plane.

377
00:25:33,096 --> 00:25:34,184
每个人都好吗?
Everybody okay?

378
00:25:34,228 --> 00:25:36,317
请安静。大家听好了!
Quiet, please. Everybody, listen up!

379
00:25:36,360 --> 00:25:38,841
我要所有人马上下飞机!
I need everybody off the plane now!

380
00:25:38,885 --> 00:25:40,408
我们要走哪条路?
Which way are we going?

381
00:25:40,451 --> 00:25:43,585
每一个人,安静。到前面去。到前面去。
Everybody, quiet. Go to the front. Go to the front.

382
00:25:43,629 --> 00:25:46,457
我要你们马上离开这架飞机!
I need you all off this plane now!

383
00:25:48,764 --> 00:25:53,789
我只是想知道…-别担心你的东西。-你需要呼吸。
I just wanna know what... - Don't worry about your stuff. - You need to breathe.

384
00:25:53,813 --> 00:25:55,118
挪到前面去。
Get moved to the front.

385
00:25:55,162 --> 00:25:56,163
好吧，深呼吸。
Okay, just breathe.

386
00:25:56,206 --> 00:25:58,513
邦妮?——两个!
- Bonnie? - Two!

387
00:25:58,557 --> 00:26:01,124
我们有两个。先生,两个。
We have two. Sir, two.

388
00:26:01,168 --> 00:26:03,474
-好吧，走吧。-好吧，来吧。移动,移动。
- Okay, just go. - Okay, come on. Move, move.

389
00:26:03,518 --> 00:26:05,912
让我们冷静地下飞机。
Let's calmly exit the plane.

390
00:26:05,955 --> 00:26:08,262
大家保持冷静。让我过去。
Everybody, stay calm. Let me through.

391
00:26:08,305 --> 00:26:10,003
-快点，邦妮-哦，是的。
- Hurry, Bonnie. - Oh, yes.

392
00:26:10,046 --> 00:26:11,918
排成一行，走过去。来吧。
In a single line, come on through. Come on.

393
00:26:11,961 --> 00:26:14,094
保持冷静!走吧!移动,移动。
Be calm! Go! Move, move.

394
00:26:17,140 --> 00:26:19,186
请靠一边去。请靠一边去。
Please move to the side. Please move to the side.

395
00:26:29,109 --> 00:26:32,286
好吧，坐下。双臂交叉，像这样。
Okay, sit down. Fold your arms, like this.

396
00:26:33,896 --> 00:26:35,376
双臂交叉，坐下。
Arms crossed, sit down.

397
00:26:59,530 --> 00:27:01,097
- 119航班。-我会打给你的
- Flight 119. - Uh, I'll call you.

398
00:27:01,141 --> 00:27:02,838
我们知道什么，西德尼?
What do we know, Sydney?

399
00:27:02,882 --> 00:27:06,233
先生，我们在菲律宾西部的某个地方丢了。
Well, sir, we lost it somewhere west of the Philippines.

400
00:27:06,276 --> 00:27:10,411
——丢了?-该飞机在当地时间5点16分要求上升高度。
- Lost? - The plane requested a higher altitude at 5:16 a.m. local.

401
00:27:10,454 --> 00:27:13,849
19分23秒后，所有通讯都停止了。
Nineteen minutes, 23 seconds later, all communication stopped.

402
00:27:13,893 --> 00:27:21,683
马尼拉空中交通管制中心一直在雷达上监视他们，直到当地时间凌晨5点43分，飞机下降到2万英尺以下，失去了所有联系。
Manila ATC had them on radar until 5:43 a.m. local when the plane dipped below 20,000 feet and lost all contact.

403
00:27:21,727 --> 00:27:23,685
马上给我接大卫·斯卡斯代尔。
Get me David Scarsdale, right now.

404
00:27:23,729 --> 00:27:27,863
我们有一些割伤和擦伤，但是，我想大家都很慌乱。
Um, we have some cuts and bruises, but, um, I think everyone's just pretty rattled.

405
00:27:27,907 --> 00:27:29,386
有人有手机信号吗?
Anyone have cell service?

406
00:27:29,430 --> 00:27:30,431
不。没有一个人。
No. No one.

407
00:27:31,650 --> 00:27:33,652
我们该拿犯人怎么办?
What do we do about the prisoner?

408
00:27:33,695 --> 00:27:35,349
我不知道。这对我来说是个新问题。
I don't know. That's a new one for me.

409
00:27:36,480 --> 00:27:41,616
嗯…我看见他在看警官的钥匙，所以我就拿走了。
Um... I saw him eyeing the officer's keys, so I took them.

410
00:27:42,225 --> 00:27:43,226
他危险吗?
Is he dangerous?

411
00:27:46,882 --> 00:27:48,841
他因谋杀指控被引渡。
He's being extradited on a murder charge.

412
00:27:49,755 --> 00:27:53,889
官……警官说，是的，他可能很危险。
The officer... The officer said, yeah, he might be dangerous.

413
00:27:56,022 --> 00:28:02,028
听着，我们只要盯着他让他和其他乘客分开，好吗?
Look, we just keep an eye on him and keep him separate from the other passengers, okay?

414
00:28:02,071 --> 00:28:03,203
尽你最大的努力。
Just try your best.

415
00:28:03,246 --> 00:28:04,639
——好的。-好吧。
- Okay. - All right.

416
00:28:04,683 --> 00:28:06,815
在这里。我觉得你应该留着这些。
Here. I think you should hold on to these.

417
00:28:08,948 --> 00:28:10,514
——好的。我们走吧。——好的。
- Okay. Let's go. - Okay.

418
00:28:10,558 --> 00:28:11,646
是的,好的。
Yeah, okay.

419
00:28:12,821 --> 00:28:14,344
水……只是没有。
Water... Just nowhere.

420
00:28:16,042 --> 00:28:17,913
-怎么回事?-告诉我们。
- What's going on? - Tell us something.

421
00:28:17,957 --> 00:28:19,610
是的。我们需要信息。
Yeah. We need information.

422
00:28:19,654 --> 00:28:21,482
我们能得到一些真实的答案吗?
Can we please get some real answers?

423
00:28:21,525 --> 00:28:26,966
-肯定有什么…-好了，各位…每个人都…听着，听着。
- There's gotta be some thing... - Okay, everybody... Everybody... Listen, listen up.

424
00:28:27,009 --> 00:28:29,751
我要感谢大家的合作。
I want to thank you all for your cooperation.

425
00:28:29,795 --> 00:28:32,798
我为我们刚刚经历的一切感到抱歉，我知道你们都有疑问。
I'm sorry for what we just had to go through, and I know you all have questions.

426
00:28:32,841 --> 00:28:33,973
-是的。-是的。
- Yeah. - Yeah.

427
00:28:34,016 --> 00:28:35,191
情况是这样的。
So, here's the situation.

428
00:28:36,845 --> 00:28:41,763
我们被闪电击中了，主电源和通讯都坏了。
We got hit by lightning and our main power and comms are down.

429
00:28:41,807 --> 00:28:45,549
好吧，到目前为止，还没办法求救。
Okay, so, as of now, there's no way of calling for help.

430
00:28:45,593 --> 00:28:48,378
什么?你在开玩笑吧。没有办法吗?没有办法吗?
What? You're kidding. No way? No way?

431
00:28:48,422 --> 00:28:53,732
我现在需要大家做的是，听好了…-为什么?-保持冷静。
What I need everybody to do right now, listen up... - How come? - Is remain calm.

432
00:28:53,775 --> 00:29:01,672
好吧?等飞机冷却下来，我们就回去，拿上东西，喝点水然后想想接下来要做什么。
All right? Once the plane cools down, we're gonna get back on there, we're gonna get our things, get some water and we're gonna figure out what we're gonna do.

433
00:29:01,696 --> 00:29:03,132
你知道我们在哪里吗?
Do you know where we are?

434
00:29:03,176 --> 00:29:07,397
是的，我们认为我们在菲律宾南部的达沃附近。
Yeah, we think that we're near Davao in the southern Philippines.

435
00:29:08,442 --> 00:29:10,052
-你觉得呢?-我们认为。
- You think? - We think.

436
00:29:10,096 --> 00:29:17,756
-非常让人放心。-请放心，我和机组人员会尽一切努力确保你安全离开这里。
- Very reassuring. - Rest assured, me and the crew are gonna do everything we can to make sure that we get you out of here safely.

437
00:29:17,799 --> 00:29:20,280
好吧?好的。谢谢你！
All right? Okay. Thank you.

438
00:29:20,323 --> 00:29:21,977
好吧，来吧。
Okay, come on.

439
00:29:24,153 --> 00:29:25,676
-嘿，特里。-嗨。
- Hey, Terry. - Hey.

440
00:29:25,720 --> 00:29:27,461
各位，这是大卫·斯卡斯代尔。
Everyone, this is David Scarsdale.

441
00:29:27,504 --> 00:29:30,725
他专门研究企业战略和危机管理。
He specializes in corporate strategy and crisis management.

442
00:29:30,769 --> 00:29:33,119
-新年快乐。-希望如此。
- Happy New Year. - Let's hope so.

443
00:29:33,162 --> 00:29:34,685
这是最后的联络点吗?
Is this the last point of contact?

444
00:29:34,729 --> 00:29:35,774
是的，它是。
Yes, it is.

445
00:29:35,817 --> 00:29:37,166
那是一场该死的风暴。
That's a hell of a storm.

446
00:29:37,210 --> 00:29:38,864
哪个白痴让他们飞过去的?
What idiot sent them flying through that?

447
00:29:38,907 --> 00:29:40,691
这是航空公司的规定。
It's airline protocol.

448
00:29:40,735 --> 00:29:42,824
飞行很轻松。这是最有效的路线。
Flight was light. It was the most efficient route.

449
00:29:42,868 --> 00:29:44,565
我以为他们能从上面飞过。
I thought they could fly above it.

450
00:29:44,608 --> 00:29:47,437
你认为呢?怎么，你他妈也是气象学家吗?
You thought? What, are you a fucking meteorologist, too?

451
00:29:47,481 --> 00:29:48,743
你节省了多少燃料?
How much fuel did you save?

452
00:29:48,787 --> 00:29:50,484
约12000美元。
About $12,000.

453
00:29:50,527 --> 00:29:53,356
好,祝贺你。这还不算这笔生意的小费。
Well, congratulations. That's barely tip money on this deal.

454
00:29:53,400 --> 00:29:55,881
时间不等人。每一分钟都很重要。
The clock is ticking. Every minute matters.

455
00:29:55,924 --> 00:30:01,625
如果那架飞机在海上迫降，或者迫降，我们可以把那几分钟算作生命的逝去或获救。明白了吗?
If that plane ditched at sea, or crash landed, we can count those minutes in lives lost or saved. Got it?

456
00:30:01,669 --> 00:30:04,715
好吧，那我该怎么办?打电话给军队?美国资产?
Okay, so, what can I do? Call the military? US assets?

457
00:30:04,759 --> 00:30:05,934
你最好的选择是什么?
What are your best options?

458
00:30:05,978 --> 00:30:09,895
在那个地方，现在只有一个选择。
Well, in that part of the world, there's only one option right now.

459
00:30:09,938 --> 00:30:11,070
那是什么?
What's that?

460
00:30:11,113 --> 00:30:12,308
你会想让律师离开这里的。
You're gonna want the lawyers out of here.

461
00:30:12,332 --> 00:30:13,812
它很好。告诉我。
It's fine. Tell me.

462
00:30:14,943 --> 00:30:17,250
私人资产。我已经很喜欢了。
Private assets. I'm already into it.

463
00:30:17,293 --> 00:30:21,907
——雇佣军?-特里…菲律宾不是阿马尔菲海岸。
- Mercenaries? - Terry... The Philippines are not the Amalfi Coast.

464
00:30:21,950 --> 00:30:26,955
现在，我需要一个小组为各种可能的情况准备新闻稿。
Now, I need a group working on press releases for every possible scenario.

465
00:30:26,999 --> 00:30:29,305
像马航370一样消失了。
A ghosting like Malaysia 370.

466
00:30:29,349 --> 00:30:31,873
迫降，无人生还。
A crash landing with no survivors.

467
00:30:31,917 --> 00:30:33,701
有要求的劫机。
A hijacking with demands.

468
00:30:33,744 --> 00:30:36,486
如果你除夕有安排，我刚取消了。
If you have plans for New Year's Eve, I just canceled them.

469
00:30:36,530 --> 00:30:38,880
再远一点。是的，一直到最后。
A little further. Yeah, right to the end.

470
00:30:38,924 --> 00:30:41,274
-尽量紧。-是的。
- Tight as we can. - Yeah.

471
00:30:41,317 --> 00:30:43,363
为什么我们就不能待在飞机里?
Why can't we just stay inside the plane?

472
00:30:43,406 --> 00:30:46,235
既安全又干燥。
It's safe and dry.

473
00:30:46,279 --> 00:30:50,936
这是个好问题，先生…辛克莱。马特·辛克莱。
Well, that's a good question, Mister, uh... Sinclair. Matt Sinclair.

474
00:30:50,979 --> 00:30:55,854
如果没有空调，那架飞机会在太阳下烤熟的。
Well, without air conditioning, that plane is gonna cook in the sun.

475
00:30:57,464 --> 00:31:02,208
所以，我们最好在这里，有遮蔽处，有微风。
So, we're better off out here, with the shelter and a breeze.

476
00:31:02,251 --> 00:31:08,083
马特·辛克莱，你去的时候，能过来帮忙保护一下吗?
Hey, while you're there, you wanna step in, help secure that, Matt Sinclair?

477
00:31:08,127 --> 00:31:16,091
好吧，如果你们在包里，找到了任何东西比如杀虫剂，防晒霜，食物，请分享。好吧?
Okay, if you're in your bags, you find anything like, uh, bug spray, sunscreen, food, please share. All right?

478
00:31:19,747 --> 00:31:20,966
Gaspare先生。
Mr. Gaspare.

479
00:31:28,582 --> 00:31:33,674
嗯…看来我们把自己弄得有点乱了。
Well... Looks like we've got ourselves in a bit of a mess here.

480
00:31:37,896 --> 00:31:42,944
所以，我不太确定我们该拿你怎么办。
And so, I'm not quite sure what we're supposed to do with you.

481
00:31:42,988 --> 00:31:45,338
说实话，我有点惊讶你还在这里。
To be honest, I'm a bit surprised you're still here.

482
00:31:46,905 --> 00:31:50,212
你以为我蠢到在我不知道的丛林里逃跑吗?
You think I'm fucking stupid enough to try and escape in a jungle I don't know?

483
00:31:51,561 --> 00:31:52,606
在手铐吗?
In handcuffs?

484
00:31:53,912 --> 00:31:54,913
除非你主动提出。
Unless you're offering.

485
00:31:57,872 --> 00:31:59,004
我觉得我做不到。
I don't think I can do that.

486
00:32:01,397 --> 00:32:03,008
那我们就没什么好谈的了。
Then we have nothing to talk about.

487
00:32:14,019 --> 00:32:15,150
大便。
Shit.

488
00:32:17,500 --> 00:32:22,375
这就是40安培保险丝被足够的能量撞击后的结果，足以点亮一座城市。
This is what happens when a 40-amp fuse gets hit with enough juice to light a city.

489
00:32:23,419 --> 00:32:24,551
看看吧，伙计。
Check it out, man.

490
00:32:28,207 --> 00:32:29,512
收音机呢?
What about the radio?

491
00:32:32,211 --> 00:32:34,735
看这里。哦,不。
Let's see here. Oh, no.

492
00:32:35,649 --> 00:32:37,303
油炸，融化。
It's fried, melted.

493
00:32:37,346 --> 00:32:38,391
应答器呢?
And the transponder?

494
00:32:40,654 --> 00:32:42,351
没有电很难分辨。
It's hard to tell without the power.

